SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 770
By Seal
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Mia Woodrick on
being named to the TSWA Class A All-State
soccer team.
WHEREAS, we are pleased to recognize and commend those successful high school
athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to Tennessee and serve as
exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is senior Mia Woodrick of Pigeon Forge High
School, an athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who has proven herself a
formidable competitor on the field; and
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Sports Writers Association (TSWA) recently named
goalkeeper Mia Woodrick to the 2025 Class A All-State soccer team in recognition of her
excellence and her display of drive and determination; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Woodrick epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as she
has achieved a high level of success in sports while evincing great character both on and off the
soccer pitch; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Woodrick's notable achievement is a source of great pride for her
family, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Mia Woodrick is a winner both on and off the field of play, and her
dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect, admiration, and commendation of
this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Mia Woodrick of Pigeon
SJR0770
